The paper discusses the limitations of standardized tests as benchmarks for measuring the progress of artificial intelligence systems in understanding basic science. This topic falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the specific features of the Physics subject SAT, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves understanding physical concepts and images. Additionally, the paper mentions the need for better natural language processing (cs.CL) benchmarks, which could also be a relevant sub-category.
